{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2500698b-dae7-4b6a-9bd8-bb6913819898","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer entirely.** That's why `vstest.console` can no longer discover your tests.\n\n### What changed\n\n- **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** defaulted to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) but still shipped a VSTest adapter bridge.\n- **MSTest.Sdk 4.x** removed that bridge completely. MTP is now the **only** supported runner.\n\n### How to fix your CI\n\n**Option A (recommended):** Replace `vstest.console` with `dotnet test`. It supports MTP natively:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n**Option B:** If you must keep `vstest.console`, pin back to MSTest.Sdk **3.8.x** (your last working version).\n\nOption A is the path forward — `vstest.console` is effectively legacy for MSTest 4.x projects.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e5a6736b-3509-4a21-9393-4c17bd3ee2fd","outputTokens":218},"id":"75043b4b-1124-402f-8703-86567be751e6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:33:33.513Z","parentId":"7327008b-2e95-42bb-a487-6dc3798955c4"}
